                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Alpha particle mesurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "1USABRK"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "1USABRK"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 88-Inch Cyclotron at Berkeley."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 3-in. diam 3-in. long NaI(Tl) crystal and a",
                "400-channel pulse-height analyzer. A collection of",
                "threshold detectors was used: 58Ni(n,p)58Co,",
                "59Co(n,alpha)56Mn, 65Cu(n,p)65Ni, 27Al(n,alpha)24Na,",
                "203Th(n,2n)202Tl, 127I(n,2n)126I, and 58Ni(n,2n)57Ni."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target was made of tantalum, and measured 2.5 in.",
                "in diameter and 0.25 in. thick. This dimension was",
                "adequate for stopping the alpha particles and for",
                "covering the end of the copper Faraday cup in which",
                "it was mounted."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TTM"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The experiment involved a target of a selected",
                "material, a means of measuring the beam particle",
                "current, the selected threshold detectors, a device",
                "to mount the detectors at predetermined positions,",
                "and a means to suppress secondary emission electrons",
                "from escaping the current-measuring device. Each",
                "threshold detector was counted at 3.0 cm from the",
                "actual face of the NaI crystal. The resultant",
                "gamma-ray spectra were used during the reduction of",
                "the data."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The total counts in the photopeak were corrected for",
                "decay and saturation. A correction was made for the",
                "abundance of the gamma ray for the decay scheme for",
                "each type of disintegration. The data were corrected",
                "for counting geometry and total absolute efficiency",
                "for the size of the NaI crystal, gamma-ray energies",
                "distance of the sample from the crystal, and sample",
                "size and thickness."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
